revision.text:
'''Tenzan Shrine''' (天山社 or 天山神社) refers to a group of {{ill|Shinto shrines|ja|神社|12=draft|12=draft}} located in {{ill|Saga Prefecture|ja|佐賀県|12=draft|12=draft}} on {{ill|Tenzan (Saga Prefecture)|ja|天山|12=draft|12=draft}}. These shrines are traditionally regarded as the third shrine (三宮) of {{ill|Hizen Province|ja|肥前国|12=draft|12=draft}}. There are four registered religious corporations under this name.
* {{ill|Tenzan Shrine (Ogimachi Hatada)|ja|天山神社 (小城市小城町畑田)|12=draft|12=draft}} - Upper Shrine (上宮) located at the summit of Tenzan. Situated in Hatada, Ogimachi, Saga Prefecture. * {{ill|Tenzan Shrine (Main Shrine)|ja|天山社|12=draft|12=draft}} - Known as the Lower Shrine (下宮) or Main Shrine (本宮). Located in Haruki, Ogimachi, Saga Prefecture. * {{ill|Tenzan Shrine (Ogimachi Iwakura)|ja|天山神社 (小城市小城町岩蔵)|12=draft|12=draft}} - Lower Shrine (下宮). Situated in Iwakura, Ogimachi, Saga Prefecture. * {{ill|Tenzan Shrine (Karatsu City)|ja|天山神社 (唐津市)|12=draft|12=draft}} - Lower Shrine (下宮). Located in Hirose, Kyūragi Town, Karatsu City, Saga Prefecture.
{{Disambiguation}}
{{citation needed|Tenzan Shrine}} [[simple:user:immanuelle/天山神社]]
